#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rselconp Selecting Control Points #!N #!EC #!N #!N Control 
points can be selected by doing one of the following: #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N o Select a single 
control point by simply clicking on it once. #!N #!I30 #!N 
o Select a group of control points by clicking on a 
point in the selected area and dragging the cursor around the 
desired points. #!N #!I30 #!N o Select all of the control 
points in an area by using the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Select All Control 
Points #!EF option under the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF menu. #!N #!I0 
#!N #!EF #!N #!N Note: A control point is selected automatically 
when it is created. When one control point is created, all 
other previously selected points in that area are automatically deselected. #!N 
